<span id="freeTextContainer9813730605932261259">The beginning and end of this book were fascinating but the middle is just a range of different books. The beginning story hits at a cabal or a conspiracy of Christian leaders and the end is about evangelical culture. Both were really interesting and the history was great too but mostly because Sharlet is a good writer. It did feel, however, that there were missing parts to the thread or the case to be made. I totally buy that evangelicals have had huge and possibly outsized influence on America</span>
  <span id="freeText9813730605932261259" style="display:none">The beginning and end of this book were fascinating but the middle is just a range of different books. The beginning story hits at a cabal or a conspiracy of Christian leaders and the end is about evangelical culture. Both were really interesting and the history was great too but mostly because Sharlet is a good writer. It did feel, however, that there were missing parts to the thread or the case to be made. I totally buy that evangelicals have had huge and possibly outsized influence on American culture, but I am not sure any of it is hidden or secret. </span>
